# Health

Loaded only when a health question arises. Not surfaced in casual briefings.

> **Sensitivity warning:** This file may contain bloodwork, diagnoses, medications, mental health notes. Like `finances.md`, it should never leave your machine. `.gitignore` excludes `memory/` by default.

> **How to populate:** Fill in what you actually track. Skip what you don't. If you have a Fitbit / Whoop / Oura / Apple Watch connection, the exocortex can pull baseline metrics automatically — you only need to add context the wearable doesn't capture.

